      <txt c="X" a="X" r="X" s="2" w="850" x="40" y="80" delay="0" pt="1" e="-3" align="left">A ship is at berth. The agent calls the company to say that he can speed up and ensure the Port State Control (PSC) clearance if he gives the authorities some cash.

Can the company be liable for the actions committed by the agent?</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="2" y="200" delay="0" crct="72" align="left">Yes, it is a facilitation payment</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="2" y="260" delay="0" crct="73" align="left">No, the company cannot be responsible</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="2" y="320" delay="0" crct="11" align="left">Yes, it is a bribe</txt>
